Since the bullet seems to be a `Rigidbody2D` you shouldn&#39;t use `Transform.Translate` **at all** but only change it though the `Rigidbody2D` component and in `FixedUpdate` for not breaking Physics. (See [`Rigidbody2D.MovePosition`](https://docs.unity3d.com/ScriptReference/Rigidbody2D.MovePosition.html))

Then for a bullet you almost never want to use [`AddForce`](https://docs.unity3d.com/ScriptReference/Rigidbody2D.AddForce.html) which would require to know the bullets&#39; mass and calculate the required force accordingly. 

You rathet instantly change its [`velocity`](https://docs.unity3d.com/ScriptReference/Rigidbody2D-velocity.html) so rather do something like

    // Having the correct type allows you only to reference
    // Object that actually have this type
    // And second you don&#39;t need `GetComponent` on runtime
    public Rigidbody2D PrefabOfBullet;

    // Set the speed you want in Unity Units / second
    public float BulletSpeed = 1f;

    ...

